@startuml
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-INSPECT)
' @id(USE-DEPLOY-DIALECT)
'
' Current-side use cases for /mdd-deploy, derived from the implemented
' code: templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL (steps 1/4/6) + its WORKFLOW_SKILLS
' entry, the .claude/.codex/skills/mdd-deploy/SKILL.md mirrors
' materialized by `mdd init`, the extended templates::MDD_RENDER_SKILL
' step, and .mdd/docs/deploy-profile.md. Standalone utility, a sibling
' of /mdd-render, NOT routed into any gate.
'
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE, "Implemented in templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL: /mdd-deploy produces a deployment diagram + secure-by-default generated IaC in the operator-CONFIRMED dialect (Bicep XOR Terraform, one per run — step 6) + a STOP-gated runbook for azure-container-apps, pausing with a blocking clarification on ambiguity, on any go-live landmine (step 3), AND to confirm the IaC dialect before writing anything (step 4). Executes no deploy command (never az/docker/terraform/brew).")
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-INSPECT, "Implemented: templates::MDD_RENDER_SKILL rasterizes .mdd/deploy/**/*.puml to .mdd/rendered/deploy/**/*.svg. Additive, non-gating.")
' @desc(USE-DEPLOY-DIALECT, "Implemented in templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL step 4 (+ deploy-profile.md \"IaC dialect — operator-confirmed, one per run\"): the dialect is exactly one of bicep or terraform per run; the skill resolves it from the description and BLOCKS for an explicit operator confirmation before writing ANY deploy artifact (diagram.puml, generated IaC, runbook.md). No silent default — an unspecified/unconfirmed dialect halts the skill; same blocking discipline as the landmine pause, never a buried runbook STOP note. Terraform enforces the same invariants + secure-by-default posture as Bicep (full parity); only structure differs (main.tf + modules + azurerm provider + remote state backend).")
title /mdd-deploy deployment guidance — use cases (current)

left to right direction

actor "Operator" as Op

rectangle "mdd toolchain (utility, outside the parity gate)" {
  usecase "Guide an Azure Container Apps\ndeployment via a diagram,\nrunbook, and generated IaC" as Guide
  usecase "Choose & CONFIRM the IaC dialect\n(Bicep XOR Terraform) before any\nartifact is written — no silent default" as Dialect
  usecase "Inspect the generated\ndeployment diagram as SVG" as Inspect
}

Op --> Guide
Op --> Dialect
Op --> Inspect

Guide ..> Dialect : <<include>>
Guide ..> Inspect : <<extend>>

note bottom of Guide
  Implemented in templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL:
  v1 supports only azure-container-apps
  (../atlas-ate-server); any other target is
  rejected. Reads MDD models + the target repo
  read-only. PAUSES with a BLOCKING clarification
  (step 3) on ambiguity OR a statically detectable
  go-live landmine — never a buried runbook STOP
  note. Writes the deployment diagram + runbook +
  SECURE-BY-DEFAULT generated IaC in the confirmed
  dialect (step 6 — no store left more network-open
  than its peers; migrations-before-traffic stays a
  documented procedural tradeoff), then reports and
  STOPS. Never runs az/docker/terraform/brew. The
  diagram stereotypes are documentation only — NOT
  the gated security-marker mechanism.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE.
end note

note bottom of Dialect
  Implemented in templates::MDD_DEPLOY_SKILL step 4.
  Mandatory <<include>>: guidance cannot proceed
  until the dialect is explicitly confirmed. One
  dialect per run (Bicep XOR Terraform). FULL
  PARITY — both dialects enforce the identical
  invariant checklist and secure-by-default posture;
  only IaC structure differs. No silent default.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-GUIDANCE.
end note

note bottom of Inspect
  Not a gate. /mdd-validate, /mdd-review and the
  /mdd-cycle parity loop never read .mdd/deploy/.
  Realized by SEQ-DEPLOY-INSPECT.
end note
@enduml
